1
00:00:00,520 --> 00:00:02,960
We have an annual trip to the hot springs.

2
00:00:02,960 --> 00:00:06,100
I've gotten super close to Ureshino-san
on this trip.

3
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:09,060
- I'll tell you more later.
- Sure, tell me.

4
00:00:09,060 --> 00:00:14,075
Did you and Ureshino-san use to date?

5
00:00:14,075 --> 00:00:17,615
I got the feeling you weren't just friends.

6
00:00:17,615 --> 00:00:20,910
It's a relationship
you can't describe through words.

7
00:00:20,910 --> 00:00:26,685
But if I said that,
Kusaka-kun would probably loathe me.

8
00:00:27,490 --> 00:00:30,300
I won't hesitate to invite you out
from now on.

9
00:00:32,210 --> 00:00:36,890
If only I could be true to these feelings,

10
00:00:36,890 --> 00:00:39,370
things would be so much easier.

11
00:00:48,930 --> 00:00:53,490
My desires are about to explode.

12
00:00:56,530 --> 00:00:58,130
Huh?

13
00:00:58,130 --> 00:01:00,550
Let me in.

14
00:01:03,060 --> 00:01:04,770
Hey.

15
00:01:06,290 --> 00:01:09,870
Why do you think I called for you?

16
00:01:30,457 --> 00:01:33,020
- "Something" shochu?
- I don't know.

17
00:01:33,020 --> 00:01:35,525
- Let's fix our makeup.
- Okay.

18
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:40,650
Mihono-san.

19
00:01:40,650 --> 00:01:43,100
Oh. She's already asleep.

20
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,310
Seriously?

21
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:46,340
She must have been tired.

22
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:49,480
- Let her sleep.
- Yeah.

23
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:53,220
That's why I said no!

24
00:01:54,565 --> 00:01:57,030
I wonder if Ureshino-san can drink a lot.

25
00:01:57,030 --> 00:01:58,405
Who knows?

26
00:01:58,405 --> 00:02:01,325
- I wonder what he's like drunk.
- Right?

27
00:02:05,245 --> 00:02:06,520
Any predictions?

28
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:09,230
- Let's see...
- Hey!

29
00:02:09,230 --> 00:02:11,885
I think he pretends to have a low tolerance,

30
00:02:11,885 --> 00:02:13,567
but drinks a bunch.

31
00:02:13,567 --> 00:02:16,703
- A bunch. I see it.
- Right?

32
00:02:16,703 --> 00:02:19,130
I get that feeling, too.

33
00:02:21,195 --> 00:02:24,199
- All right, I'm ready.
- Me too. Let's go.

34
00:02:25,490 --> 00:02:27,600
All right.

35
00:02:34,355 --> 00:02:35,880
We're drinking tonight!

36
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:38,190
Yeah!

37
00:02:41,990 --> 00:02:44,870
That was dangerous.

38
00:02:46,290 --> 00:02:48,680
You overreacted.

39
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:51,840
Unbelievable.

40
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:21,400
Your phone.

41
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,730
Ignore it.

42
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:33,110
That's more like it.

43
00:04:15,465 --> 00:04:17,320
Morning, Kusaka-kun.

44
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:19,490
Good morning.

45
00:04:21,028 --> 00:04:24,080
Sorry about yesterday.
I fell fast asleep.

46
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,600
No,

47
00:04:26,395 --> 00:04:27,460
it's fine.

48
00:04:27,460 --> 00:04:30,520
Um, is your foot okay?

49
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:35,330
Oh, yeah. I bought a Band-Aid
at the store earlier, so I'm fine.

50
00:04:35,330 --> 00:04:36,585
Thanks.

51
00:04:36,585 --> 00:04:40,260
I see. That's good then.

52
00:04:47,575 --> 00:04:50,860
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

53
00:04:52,115 --> 00:04:54,320
Good morning.

54
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:57,220
- Ureshino-san!
- Oh, good morning, Yuri-chan.

55
00:04:57,220 --> 00:04:59,480
Jeez, what happened yesterday?

56
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:01,915
Sorry, I fell asleep before I knew it.

57
00:05:01,915 --> 00:05:03,670
We were waiting for you the whole time!

58
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:06,220
Really? Sorry, sorry.

59
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:08,890
Please sit.

60
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:13,900
♫ It's hard to resist the thing
that I've missed for so long ♫

61
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:15,720
♫ So long ♫

62
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:19,440
♫ Can't remember what it's like,
Just remember I need it ♫

63
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:22,040
♫ I need it ♫

64
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:25,860
♫ Even if I'm wrong,
the train of thoughts I'm always in the right ♫

65
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:28,030
♫ In the right ♫

66
00:05:28,030 --> 00:05:31,520
♫ Gotta trust the guy,
yeah, no matter what happens ♫

67
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:33,890
♫ What happens ♫

68
00:05:33,890 --> 00:05:38,120
♫ You're not what I thought you were ♫

69
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:40,050
♫ You were ♫

70
00:05:40,050 --> 00:05:43,420
♫ To think I can't find a cure ♫

71
00:05:43,420 --> 00:05:46,060
♫ Find a cure ♫

72
00:05:46,060 --> 00:05:52,210
♫ Ooh, you're not what I thought ♫

73
00:05:52,210 --> 00:05:57,390
♫ Ooh, you're not what I thought ♫

74
00:05:57,390 --> 00:05:59,660
♫ Thought, thought ♫

75
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:04,140
♫ Thought, thought ♫

76
00:06:04,140 --> 00:06:08,210
♫ Thought ♫

77
00:06:09,610 --> 00:06:17,010
[If Only You Weren't the One]

78
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:23,150
[Episode 5]

79
00:06:48,010 --> 00:06:52,130
The heat from that day
still hasn't cooled down.

80
00:07:14,245 --> 00:07:18,410
Hey, aren't you staying over too much lately?

81
00:07:19,140 --> 00:07:20,770
Can't I?

82
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:32,905
Right now, we're closer than
we've ever been.

83
00:07:34,865 --> 00:07:37,535
- Get off me.
- No.

84
00:07:37,535 --> 00:07:41,045
- I can't cook.
- Stir properly.

85
00:07:43,985 --> 00:07:48,060
Hey... This is even harder.

86
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:49,800
Right.

87
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,940
Oh, this works.

88
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:04,170
That's why...

89
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:15,950
Don't look away.

90
00:08:18,980 --> 00:08:23,540
all sorts of things
have become so clear.

91
00:08:49,545 --> 00:08:51,590
You're finally awake?

92
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:54,185
Yeah. Morning.

93
00:08:55,020 --> 00:08:56,840
Morning.

94
00:08:58,485 --> 00:09:01,840
Your phone was ringing last night, too.

95
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:03,490
Huh?

96
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,980
Is everything okay?

97
00:09:10,170 --> 00:09:11,910
What's okay?

98
00:09:14,570 --> 00:09:16,740
Is it a girl?

99
00:09:18,950 --> 00:09:20,570
Hmm.

100
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:26,190
It's nothing like that.

101
00:09:32,430 --> 00:09:35,280
If you have time, eat before you go.

102
00:09:41,990 --> 00:09:44,360
Whoa, looks good.

103
00:09:45,890 --> 00:09:47,590
Huh?

104
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:49,450
Don't you prefer rice in the morning?

105
00:09:49,450 --> 00:09:53,585
Yeah. I usually do, but sometimes it's fine.

106
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,680
Is that so?

107
00:09:57,710 --> 00:09:59,510
Huh?

108
00:09:59,510 --> 00:10:01,634
What about breakfast?

109
00:10:01,634 --> 00:10:04,990
I can whip up some rice balls or miso soup.

110
00:10:04,990 --> 00:10:06,585
Oh...

111
00:10:06,585 --> 00:10:09,025
Nah, I'm more of a bread guy.

112
00:10:10,335 --> 00:10:12,600
No, it's not like that.

113
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:15,500
I was in the mood for bread.

114
00:10:17,060 --> 00:10:19,280
Oh?

115
00:10:20,905 --> 00:10:24,880
Come on. I'm serious.

116
00:10:25,650 --> 00:10:28,890
Well, either way is fine.

117
00:10:28,890 --> 00:10:30,360
Let's eat.

118
00:11:05,690 --> 00:11:08,070
Aw, man.

119
00:11:08,070 --> 00:11:12,690
I wonder why we aren't dating.

120
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:21,230
If I fall for you seriously again...

121
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:27,860
I think I like you.

122
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:33,700
You're so cute, Miporin.

123
00:11:50,830 --> 00:11:53,630
I wonder if we'll drift apart.

124
00:12:01,335 --> 00:12:04,430
Hey, walk a bit further away.

125
00:12:04,430 --> 00:12:06,110
What's this all of a sudden?

126
00:12:06,110 --> 00:12:09,390
- Don't cling to me in the office.
- I'm not.

127
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:11,389
People will find out we came together.

128
00:12:11,389 --> 00:12:12,845
So what? It's fine.

129
00:12:12,845 --> 00:12:15,485
It's not fine.

130
00:12:21,295 --> 00:12:22,770
Good morning.

131
00:12:22,770 --> 00:12:25,565
- Morning.
- Good morning.

132
00:12:28,555 --> 00:12:30,620
- Ureshino-san.
- Yes?

133
00:12:30,620 --> 00:12:33,355
Regarding today's meeting with the client,

134
00:12:33,355 --> 00:12:36,423
is the meeting in the lobby at 12 okay?

135
00:12:36,423 --> 00:12:40,760
Sure. It should take about 10 minutes
by taxi, so that's fine.

136
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:45,365
Understood. I'll prepare the proposal
on my end.

137
00:12:45,365 --> 00:12:47,375
Thank you.

138
00:12:54,885 --> 00:12:58,570
I might be able to get a contract
from my old company.

139
00:12:58,570 --> 00:13:02,500
- Huh?
- They said they're considering a company trip.

140
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:05,418
It's a pretty big company,
so it'd be a big deal.

141
00:13:05,418 --> 00:13:08,510
Wow. Really? That's amazing.

142
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:11,224
It's not decided yet, though.

143
00:13:11,224 --> 00:13:16,050
But for now, Kusaka-san and I
are in charge of selling to them.

144
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:17,620
The two of you?

145
00:13:17,620 --> 00:13:19,035
Yeah.

146
00:13:19,035 --> 00:13:23,455
We'll have to work together
and do our best.

147
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:33,550
So pyramids are the best for the first day, right?
[Travel Plan]

148
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:37,400
- Oh, really.
- Regarding the first day...

149
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:40,225
Well, the weather...

150
00:13:40,225 --> 00:13:43,030
The Karnak Temple
is all the rage this year.

151
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,430
What's there?

152
00:13:44,430 --> 00:13:47,700
- There's an obelisk.
- Oh?

153
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:49,470
Yes, it is.

154
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:57,530
You surprised me.

155
00:13:57,530 --> 00:13:59,770
What's that face?

156
00:13:59,770 --> 00:14:03,740
Ta-da! This Friday! Isn't this crazy?
[Dinner with Ureshino-san!]

157
00:14:03,740 --> 00:14:05,220
Hm?

158
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:08,600
- What? You're having dinner?
- Exactly!

159
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:11,030
Isn't this awesome? It's crazy, right?

160
00:14:11,030 --> 00:14:12,930
- Did you invite him?
- Yes.

161
00:14:12,930 --> 00:14:16,210
I mustered up all my courage
and sent a message last night,

162
00:14:16,210 --> 00:14:17,640
but he didn't read it.

163
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:20,480
I thought about erasing the message
a thousand times,

164
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:22,400
but he replied this morning!

165
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,010
- I see.
- Yes!

166
00:14:24,010 --> 00:14:27,250
- That's great.
- Gosh, I did so well yesterday.

167
00:14:27,250 --> 00:14:31,145
The best thing I've ever done
in the last 25 years!

168
00:14:33,815 --> 00:14:38,810
Now that I think about it,
I bet girls like her are his real type.

169
00:14:40,545 --> 00:14:44,980
With a cute smile, a bright personality,

170
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:49,985
straightforward, and open.

171
00:14:49,985 --> 00:14:52,265
A pleasant girl.

172
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:19,930
Not tainted like I am.

173
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:29,830
A girl who doesn't
put on a hypocritical front.

174
00:15:33,405 --> 00:15:36,650
The one who becomes Eisei's "real love"

175
00:15:36,650 --> 00:15:39,710
is probably a girl like this.

176
00:15:59,175 --> 00:16:02,430
No, I know.

177
00:16:02,430 --> 00:16:06,160
This isn't worth reporting to you.
And Yuri-chan is a really sweet girl.

178
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:10,770
But Yuri-chan with Eisei Ureshino is a waste.

179
00:16:10,770 --> 00:16:15,530
I'm worried, you know. Why that guy of all people?

180
00:16:15,530 --> 00:16:17,930
But you know, I get it.

181
00:16:17,930 --> 00:16:21,720
He's a handsome guy,
and his smile is to die for.

182
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:23,110
Yeah, I get it.

183
00:16:23,110 --> 00:16:26,505
I really do,
but his communication skills are awful.

184
00:16:26,505 --> 00:16:30,565
Why's he playing around
just because he's popular?

185
00:16:32,630 --> 00:16:35,040
Well, calm down first.

186
00:16:36,850 --> 00:16:38,340
Okay.

187
00:16:43,315 --> 00:16:46,220
So, in the end, you like him, right?

188
00:16:46,220 --> 00:16:47,895
Huh?

189
00:16:47,895 --> 00:16:49,265
Huh?

190
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:51,750
Huh?

191
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:57,740
What?

192
00:16:57,740 --> 00:17:00,290
You're scaring me.

193
00:17:00,290 --> 00:17:02,035
Just admit it.

194
00:17:02,035 --> 00:17:07,085
You want to be the main girl of
that playboy with bad communication skills.

195
00:17:08,090 --> 00:17:10,580
To be his girlfriend, right?

196
00:17:12,675 --> 00:17:14,750
Man, I see.

197
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:18,100
I haven't said anything.

198
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:22,600
No affirmation speaks more eloquently
than silence.

199
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:24,785
Sorry, what does that mean?

200
00:17:24,785 --> 00:17:27,875
It's love, right?

201
00:17:30,565 --> 00:17:33,450
- Okay, you admit it.
- No, I'm not admitting it.

202
00:17:33,450 --> 00:17:34,960
I'm not admitting it.

203
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:37,375
Then, what? Are you playing around too?

204
00:17:37,375 --> 00:17:40,445
No, but...

205
00:17:40,445 --> 00:17:45,330
Well, I'm telling you, I don't know.

206
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,017
First of all,

207
00:17:49,017 --> 00:17:52,177
handle your current relationship.

208
00:17:53,235 --> 00:17:58,975
You know, for the last 10 years,
the same thing's been controlling you.

209
00:17:58,975 --> 00:18:01,950
If you can't tell if it's play or not,

210
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:05,495
maybe you should distance yourself
from Eisei Ureshino

211
00:18:05,495 --> 00:18:08,535
to figure out your own feelings.

212
00:18:25,770 --> 00:18:29,180
[Eisei Ureshino]

213
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:39,770
Hello?

214
00:18:42,230 --> 00:18:44,620
Not really.

215
00:18:44,620 --> 00:18:47,420
I had lunch with a friend.

216
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:53,330
I have time, but...

217
00:18:56,975 --> 00:19:02,140
The more I try to understand,
the more confused I get.

218
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,370
Here I am.

219
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:21,870
I'm losing...

220
00:19:24,090 --> 00:19:26,850
my ability to think straight.

221
00:19:29,403 --> 00:19:32,040
All right. It's Friday, so let's get drinks.

222
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,700
Yeah, let's go!

223
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:36,410
- But it's crowded everywhere today.
- True.

224
00:19:36,410 --> 00:19:38,560
- What's for dinner?
- Barbecue!

225
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:41,780
Oh, yeah!

226
00:19:41,780 --> 00:19:44,550
- It's a sheep.
- Sheep?

227
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:46,730
Your art's awful. That's so cute.

228
00:19:46,730 --> 00:19:50,156
- But your drawing's worse, you know.
- You think so?

229
00:19:50,156 --> 00:19:52,391
This one's way cuter.

230
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:02,050
- What about this?
- Maybe I replied.

231
00:20:02,050 --> 00:20:03,430
I'm getting angry.

232
00:20:03,430 --> 00:20:05,720
Really? It's true.

233
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:07,720
Stop it!

234
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:10,030
Angry?

235
00:20:10,030 --> 00:20:12,445
No, no.

236
00:20:12,445 --> 00:20:14,374
- I'll redraw it.
- Actually try.

237
00:20:14,374 --> 00:20:16,654
Yeah, I'll be serious.

238
00:20:24,130 --> 00:20:26,000
Onuma-san.

239
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,930
Oh, Kusaka-kun.

240
00:20:27,930 --> 00:20:31,775
- Good work today.
- Good work today.

241
00:20:31,775 --> 00:20:33,480
What are you drinking?

242
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:37,415
Oh, it's coffee. To wake myself up.

243
00:20:37,415 --> 00:20:39,290
I know that feeling.

244
00:20:39,290 --> 00:20:41,980
Maybe I'll get the same.

245
00:20:49,783 --> 00:20:55,680
Um, if you have time,
let's hang out sometime.

246
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:58,358
Not just a meal after work,

247
00:20:58,358 --> 00:21:01,533
but a movie or something.

248
00:21:04,020 --> 00:21:05,620
What?

249
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:09,230
I want to learn...

250
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:14,150
more about you, Onuma-san.

251
00:21:17,435 --> 00:21:21,081
Sorry, that was sudden.
It doesn't have to be a movie, anything is fine.

252
00:21:21,081 --> 00:21:24,391
Food-hopping, visiting an amusement park...

253
00:21:24,391 --> 00:21:26,830
What else?

254
00:21:26,830 --> 00:21:28,365
A cafe?

255
00:21:28,365 --> 00:21:31,085
Oh, a fishing pond, too.

256
00:21:32,526 --> 00:21:34,800
Okay. Thank you.

257
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:36,875
I'll check my schedule.

258
00:21:36,875 --> 00:21:38,385
Okay.

259
00:21:40,690 --> 00:21:43,420
Oh, it's the section chief.

260
00:21:45,510 --> 00:21:47,080
Yes?

261
00:21:56,025 --> 00:22:00,920
You know,
Kusaka-kun is surprisingly strong mentally.

262
00:22:01,970 --> 00:22:04,320
What do you mean?

263
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:08,380
He doesn't give up even after that.

264
00:22:08,380 --> 00:22:10,490
After what?

265
00:22:11,980 --> 00:22:14,780
You really didn't notice?

266
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:21,060
I was seen...

267
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,900
going into your room.

268
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:31,290
Huh?

269
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:34,360
Miporin?

270
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:36,190
Hey!

271
00:22:36,190 --> 00:22:38,150
Miporin!

272
00:22:38,150 --> 00:22:39,515
- Miporin!
- You're too loud!

273
00:22:39,515 --> 00:22:41,925
Just shut up and get in.

274
00:22:42,590 --> 00:22:49,180
♫ We walked through the city at daybreak,
soaked by the rain ♫

275
00:22:49,180 --> 00:22:54,110
♫ You and me in the rain ♫

276
00:22:56,320 --> 00:22:58,240
Miporin, your phone.

277
00:23:00,530 --> 00:23:02,310
Ignore it.

278
00:23:03,580 --> 00:23:07,520
♫ I kept looking at you ♫

279
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:09,920
That's more like it.

280
00:23:14,690 --> 00:23:18,040
[Kusaka-kun]

281
00:23:18,860 --> 00:23:23,150
♫ Of my hand ♫

282
00:23:30,355 --> 00:23:32,000
You're my partner in crime.
[Preview]

283
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,720
Don't talk to me.

284
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:35,400
Can't you choose Kusaka?

285
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:39,810
I've never once heard you say
what you like about Eisei Ureshino.

286
00:23:39,810 --> 00:23:43,490
They say the one
who falls in love loses, don't they?

287
00:23:43,490 --> 00:23:46,340
I wonder, what do I want with Kusaka-kun?

288
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:47,920
Looks like she got rejected.

289
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:51,790
Telling her the truth is true kindness.

290
00:23:51,790 --> 00:23:54,702
With both work and love left half-hearted.

291
00:23:54,702 --> 00:23:57,327
What if we actually started dating?

292
00:23:57,327 --> 00:24:00,030
[This drama is fiction.]
